Pre-Game Insights: Kenya has won three games while losing only two in their last five T20Is; they are coming off a 4-wicket win against Nigeria following a 14-run defeat against the same opponent.
Mozambique has lost three while winning only two games in their last five fixtures; they defeated Rwanda by 5 wickets in the previous T20I encounter.
The match is part of the T20 WC Sub Regional Africa Qualifier B 2024 and will be played at Ruaraka Sports Club Ground in Nairobi on October 19 at 4:20 PM IST.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch is bowling-friendly with an average of 125 runs in the last five T20s; spinners have dominated here as compared to the pacers in the game.
Rainy conditions expected, which could impact match proceedings.
Others: KEN is the clear favorite in betting odds, with a better recent form compared to MOZ.
The probable playing XI for Kenya includes key players like Irfan Karim (wk), SR Bhudia, Pushkar Sharma, Rushabvardhan Patel (C), and others.
The probable playing XI for Mozambique includes Agostinho Navicha (wk), Jose Joao, F Nhaduate (C), and others.
